Keynote address by Mary Robinson, chair of the Elders, first female President of Ireland and former UN High Commissioner for human rights. JOHANNESBURG - Ireland's first Female President and former UN High Commissioner for human rights Mary Robinson, will on Monday give a keynote speech at the Daily Maverick's panel discussion on climate change. She's expected to argue that Africa is the continent most affected by climate change but is the least responsible for it. It kicks-off the first in a series of events centred around climate change called The Burning Planet.